'Every Rohirrim must be able to ride as if he were riding the wind, he and his horse moving together as if they were one. The best way to test this is to race.

'We have set up a course that travels from Cliving up into the southern Wold, around the edge of the cliffs, then down and back west along the road until you return to the city.

'There are thirty points to hit among numerous twists and turns and curves. You are welcome to try if you think you are up to the challenge.'
'You handle your steed well. That course is not for beginners. I am impressed you were able to navigate it.'
